missionEventData.data2: In the far reaches of the Outer Rim a rebellion is forming. A rebel cell led by the frigate Redemption and ace pilot Keyan Farlander have been striking back against the evil galactic empire. But the Emperor is at the height of his power, and even now he is marshalling his forces at the edge of the mid-rim. But help has come from the most unlikely of places. The captain of an imperial corvette has sent the rebel freedom fighters a secret message, he wishes to defect...

missionEventData.data1: Ordnance and Supply has alerted Sector Command that one of our freighters has broken down in the Rudrig sector. Your mission is to provide protection while one of our technical shuttles jumps in to repair the freighter. Ensure that both the freighter and the shuttle safely exit the system. Beware that there are pirates active in this area, ensure that they don't interfere with this operation.
Red One head to the jump point immediately, the repair shuttle is already enroute.
Shuttle Type DX9 and escort this is the Freighter Ars Opus, identify yourselves and state your intention
Ars Opus, this is Alliance Shuttle Dagger here to provide assistance.
So glad to see you! Some suspicious ships have started jumping in and out of the system. We we're starting to get worried.
Understood. Red One scan the nav buoys to see if we can get more information on these visitors. We'll assist the Opus.
Okay. Cross referencing the data.. According to the information here two groups of three fighters just left the adjoining system.
Based on the average flight time the first group should be entering the system about... now
Warning! Three fighters exiting hyperspace. They're Pirates!
Red One, the Ars Opus is still getting ready to jump. Keep those bandits off us!
Warning another group of Pirates is exiting hyperspace. Keep them busy.
Well done Red One. Once the Dagger has disengaged, we're ready to jump.
Thanks for your help Red One. See you at the rendezvous.

missionEventData.data3: Thanks to your efforts we were able to keep the Ars Opus and its critical supply of Astromech Units free from pirate hands. However High Command is still working through some discrepancies in the Ars Opus’ report…
